------------------------------------------------------------------
KEY LESSON
------------------------------------------------------------------

PDFs are text-based containers with a rich internal object model.
Comments (% lines) are invisible to viewers but fully present in
the raw bytes. Ascii85 encoded data inside a PDF comment is a
clean hiding spot because nothing in normal PDF usage puts large
encoded blobs there. When you find decoded PDF graphics operators,
read the coordinate system: different y values mean different
text layers, and challenge authors always plant decoys at higher
layers to slow you down. Always extract every layer and identify
the one that matches the real flag format before submitting.
